                    <section>
                            <h2>Compact Binaries</h2>
<div class="altpanel" style="height: 430px">
                                    <h3> Cataclysmic Variable/ Low-mass X-ray Binary</h3>
						<div class style="float: left; width: 45%" data-fragment-index='10'>
							<ul>
                                    <li><b>White dwarf / Neutron star</b> as primary:</li>
                                            
                                    <li> MS star companion</li>
								<li>Accretion (usually) via a disk:</li>
                                <ul>
                                        <li>Disk instability <em>outbursts</em>. Increase several magnitudes</li>
                                        <li style='list-style: none;'></li>

                                </ul>
                                
							</ul>
						</div>
						<figure style="float: right; width: 45%">
							<img src="images/wdns.png" />
							<figcaption>
                            <small>Credit: Rob Hynes.</small>
							</figcaption>
						</figure>
                           
						<figure style="float: right; width: 45%">
							<img src="images/halpha.svg" />
						</figure>
						</div>
                    </section>


                    <section>
						<h2>Binaries in Globular Clusters </h2>
					<ul>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='1' ><b>Globular Clusters</b>
							<ul>
                                    <li>The binary population drives the <em>dynamical evolution</em> of GCs</li>
							</ul>
							</li>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='2'><b>Cataclysmic Variables:</b>
							<ul>
                                    <!--                                    <li>Expected big sample at a <em>know distance</em>.</li>-->
                                    <li>Potentially very <em>different from field CVs</em></li>
                                    <li><span class="fragment grow" class='fragment highlight-red' data-fragment-index="5">  A lot of open questions</span></li>
                                    </ul>
                            </li>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='3'><b>Neutron Stars:</b>
							<ul>
                                    <li><em>Known distance</em> binary in GC</li>
                                    <li>Estimate equation of state (mass-radius relation)</li>
							</ul>
							</li>
                            <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='4' ><b>Gravitational Waves:</b>.
							<ul>
                                <li>White dwarf degenerate sources for <em>LISA</em></li>
							</ul>
							</li>
						</ul>

                    </section>
                    <section>

<div class="altpanel" style="height: 430px">
                                 <h2> Field CVs and GC CVs</h2>
						<div class style="float: left; width: 45%">

                                 <h3>GC CVs</h3>
                                 <ul>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='1'  >Primordial and Dynamically formed</li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='2'   >Dearth of outbursts </li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='3'   >Mainly magnetic? </li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='4'  >Period distribution?</li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='5'  >8 spectra from 4 GCs</li>
                                         </ul>
                        </div>
						<div class style="float: right; width: 45%">
                                 <h3>Field CVs</h3>
                                 <ul>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='1' >Main Sequence binary evolution</li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='2'   > 40% show outburst </li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='3'  >25% magnetic </li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='4'  > $75 \text{ min} \lesssim \text{P}_{\text{orb}}\lesssim 10 \text{ hrs} $ </li>
                                         <li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='5'  >Hundreds of spectra</li>
                                         </ul>
                        </div>

</div>

