                    <section>
						<h2>Binaries in NGC 6397 </h2>
						<h4>Known X-ray sources </h4>
					<ul>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='1' ><b>Cataclysmic Variables</b>
							<ul>
                                                            <li>15 CV <em>Candidates</em></li>
                                                            <li>Two <em>Bimodal Population:</em></li>
                                                            <ul><li>Bright and Faint (Cohn et al. 2011)</li></ul>
							</ul>
							</li>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='2'><b>Millisecond Pulsars (MSPs):</b>
							<ul>
                                    <!--                                    <li>Expected big sample at a <em>know distance</em>.</li>-->
                                    <li>One radio confirmed and one candidate </li>
                                    </ul>
                            </li>
							<li class='fragment' data-fragment-index='3'><b>Neutron Stars:</b>
							<ul>
                                    <li> One qLMXB and possibly<em> ultracompact</em> </li>
							</ul>
							</li>
					</ul>

					<p style='margin-top':5cm;>
					<h2 class='fragment' data-fragment-index='6' style='margin-top':3cm > <em>Characterize and find new binaries   </em></h2></p>



